        <section name="Introduction">

            The Java Pairing Based Cryptography Library (jPBC) is:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        a <font style="font-weight: bold;color:red">Java Porting</font> of the
                        <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/pbc/">PBC</a>
                        library which is the Pairing-Based Cryptography Library written in C and
                        developed by
                        <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/~blynn/">Ben Lynn</a>.
                        It supports symmetric and asymmetric pairing.                        
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        a <font style="font-weight: bold;color:red">Java Wrapper</font> of the
                        <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/pbc/">PBC</a>
                        library so you can delegate all the computation to the C library.
                        Look
                        <a href="./docs/pbcwrapper.html">here</a>
                        to know how to use the wrapper.
                    </p>
                </li>

            </ul>

            jPBC consists of the following modules:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-api</font> :
                    which contains the API exposed by jPBC.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-plaf</font> :
                    which contains the default API's implementation. This module contains the PBC's Java Porting.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-pbc</font> :
                    which contains the API's implementation to be used when PBC is chosen as computation engine.
                    This module contains the PBC's Java Wrapper.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-crypto</font> :
                    which contains the implementation of some cryptosystems. Go
                    <a href="./schemes/schemes.html">here</a>
                    to start.
                </li>

            </ul>
            In the jPBC distribution package each module corresponds to a
            directory where you will find the sources of the module and
            other stuff.
        </section>

